## Conventions
- Naming: snake_case / camelCase / PascalCase
- Error style: raise `DomainError` / return `ProblemDetails`
- Logging: structured JSON, correlation_id
- Testing: pytest / xUnit / Jest

## Security baseline
- Secrets only via env vars; no hardcoded keys.
- SQL only via parameterized queries / ORM.
- Input validation on every boundary.
- No `CORS(*)` with credentials in production.

## Don'ts
- Do not return ORM entities from API.
- Do not use generic `Repository<T>`.
- Do not add dependencies without lockfile update.
- Do not commit transcripts or `.env`.

## Test & run commands
- `make test`
- `make lint`
- `make run`

